<bug>
    <id>8604</id>
    <title>Decimal ip gives "Bad Request"</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">When using decimal notation for ip address (i.e. 1073428622 instead of
63.251.56.142) the server
responds with a 400-error "Bad Request".</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">Same behaviour under Linux and Solaris.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">W32 not checked.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">I'm not sure if this is by design, but 1.3 behaves as expected and delivers the
correct url.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
